:INFO
The Longest Book I Have Finished and Why It Was Worth It
The Power Broker is 1336 pages about Robert Moses, the urban planner who built \
New York over five decades and in doing so displaced hundreds of thousands of \
people. Robert Caro spent fourteen years researching it. Reading it requires \
a different kind of commitment than almost any other book I have finished. I read \
it over four months and took notes. The answer to whether it was worth the time \
is yes, but I understand the argument of every person who has not finished it.

